As I already commented, and as @zephraph agreed, S2L should have its own `DotDict` implementation and not use the one from RF 2.9. It should be named differently to avoid confusion, though. This ought to be enough:

```python
class AttrDict(dict):

    def __getattr__(self, name):
        try:
            return self[name]
        except KeyError:
            raise AttributeError(name)

    def __setattr__(self, name, value):
        self[name] = value

    def __delattr__(self, name):
        try:
            del self[name]
        except KeyError:
            raise AttributeError(name)
```

