Here's a snippet of code I used on a project to normalize the error message that gets returned (goes on your Resource class):

    def error_response(self, request, errors, response_class=None):
        # I think those are the only 2 error status codes where we provide a response body.
        if 'error' in errors:
            errors = errors['error']
        
        if isinstance(errors, ValidationError):
            errors = errors.messages
        
        if not isinstance(errors, dict):
            if not isinstance(errors, list):
                errors = [errors]
            
            errors = {'__all__': errors}
        
        errors = {'error': errors}
        
        return super(CustomModelResource, self).error_response(request, errors, response_class=response_class)

I have implemented something similar based on Javascript only using a dropdown select instead of tabs (we will have too many languages even for tabs).

![wagtail-internationalization-dropdown](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1606177/36619322-bc08e582-18ee-11e8-8274-7df36243a681.png)

You can just copy it into one of your template dirs as "wagtailadmin/pages/edit.html":

```
{% extends "wagtailadmin/pages/edit.html" %}
{% load i18n %}

{% block extra_js %}
    {{ block.super }}

    <script>
        var translatables = {};

        function change_language(active_language) {
            for( var key in translatables )
                translatables[key].map( function(obj) {
                    obj.toggle(key === active_language)
                });
        }

        $(function () {
            $('ul[class="objects"]').find('label:contains(" [")').each(function () {
                var label = $.trim($(this).text());
                var language = label.substr(label.lastIndexOf('[') + 1, 2);
                if( !(language in translatables))
                    translatables[language] = [];
                translatables[language].push($(this).closest('li'));
            });

            var s = $('<select id="language_select" style="padding:9px; width: auto; margin-left:8px;" />');
            for (var key in translatables)
                $('<option />', {value: key, text: key}).appendTo(s);
            $("ul[class='tab-nav merged']").append(s);

            $("#language_select").on('change', function () {
                change_language(this.value);
            });

            change_language("en");
        });
    </script>
{% endblock %}
```

